0data-toc-id%3D%5C%223dfb321a-058a-4d91-b8d4-25b38e52f225%5C%22%3EI%20got%20to%20enjoy%20young%20life%20child-free%20and%20still%20become%20a%20parent%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20not%20saying%20all%20parents%20automatically%20regret%20what%20they%20missed%20when%20they%20have%20kids%20at%20a%20young%20age%2C%20but%20I%20know%20some%20who%20do%20%E2%80%94%20and%20I%20might%20have%20been%20one%20of%20them.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbeing-older-parents-pros-cons-stability-energy-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHaving%20my%20daughter%20in%20my%2040s%3C%2Fa%3E%20means%20I%20don't%20resent%20my%20daughter%20for%20things%20I%20didn't%20get%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%2024%2C%20I%20was%20the%20founding%20editor%20of%20an%20entertainment%20magazine.%20If%20I'd%20had%20a%20child%20back%20then%2C%20could%20I%20have%20pulled%20the%20countless%20all-nighters%20working%20that%20I%20did%2C%20or%20attended%20all%20the%20gigs%20and%20events%20we%20covered%3F%20Unlikely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%2020s%20were%20fun%20but%20exhausting%2C%20and%20by%20the%20time%20I%20hit%20my%2040s%2C%20I%20was%20ready%20for%20a%20new%20adventure.%20More%20importantly%2C%20I%20was%20more%20secure%20in%20who%20I%20was.%20That%20meant%20I%20didn't%20sweat%20all%20the%20small%20stuff%20I%20probably%20would%20have%20if%20I%20were%20younger%20and%20trying%20to%20prove%20I%20could%20be%20the%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbecoming-a-mom-softened-my-idea-of-perfection-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eperfect%20mom%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20as%20a%20mom%20in%20my%2040s%20to%20a%20turbo%20toddler%2C%20I%20learned%20that%20a%20messy%20house%20could%20still%20be%20a%20happy%20one.%20A%20mud-covered%203-year-old%20wasn't%20naughty%20%E2%80%94%20just%20carefree.%20And%20even%20if%20my%20Christmas%20cookies%20looked%20more%20like%20Edvard%20Munch's%20%3Cem%3EScream%3C%2Fem%3E%20than%20a%20jolly%20sno