_blank%5C%22%3Eburrito%20season%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20getting%20out%20of%20the%20house%20can%20be%20hard%2C%20and%20having%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcheap-stuff-economy-prices-american-dream-housing-televisions-tariffs-trump-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estuff%20you%20do%20not%20need%3C%2Fa%3E%20dropped%20on%20your%20doorstep%20is%20a%20fun%20tiny%20luxury%20of%20our%20tech-enabled%20world.%20But%20if%20you're%20considering%20using%20a%20Klarna%20financing%20plan%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoordash-partners-with-klarna-reaction-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDoorDash%20your%20Chipotle%20order%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20maybe%20take%20a%20beat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20all%20the%20DoorDash%20fees%2C%20plus%20the%20tip%20%E2%80%94%20and%2C%20yes%2C%20you%20should%20tip%20%E2%80%94%20that%20little%20treat%20is%20going%20to%20run%20you%20quite%20a%20bit%20more%20than%20you%20bargained%20for.%20Splitting%20the%20cost%20up%20into%20four%20payments%20may%20make%20you%20feel%20better%20about%20your%20little%20indulgence%20%E2%80%94%20and%20may%20even%20encourage%20you%20to%20add%20on%20a%20second%20little%20treat.%20But%20there%20are%20some%20potential%20downsides.%20You%20might%20wind%20up%20missing%20payments%2C%20in%20which%20case%20on%20top%20of%20delivery%20fees%20and%20tip%2C%20you'll%20also%20be%20hit%20with%20late%20fees%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Foverdraft-fees-what-banks-charge%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoverdraft%20fees%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20your%20bank.%20By%20the%20end%20of%20it%20all%2C%20your%20%2420%20burrito%20could%20wind%20up%20costing%20closer%20to%20%2470.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20mean%20to%20be%20judgmental.%20If%20you%20really%20insist%20on%20paying%20for%20food%20delivery%20on%20a%20payment%20plan%2C%20you%20can.%20In%20fact%2C%20DoorDash%20and%20Klarna%20are%20betting%20you%20will.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20week%2C%20the%20delivery%20platform%20Doordash%20and%20the%20soon-to-IPO%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fklarna-ipo-employees-in-limbo-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epayment%20company%20Klarna%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fdoordash-to-partner-with-klarna-on-payment-options-for-u-s-customers-1034499278%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eannounced%20a%20partnership%3C%2Fa%3E%20through%20which%20customers%20will%20be%20able%20to%20buy%20now%2C%20pay%20later%20on%20food%20orders.%20People%20will%20have%20the%20option%20to%20pay%20right%20away%2C%20like%20normal%2C%20using%20Klarna%2C%20but%20they'll%20also%20be%20able%20to%20split%20the%20cost%20into%20four%20installment%20payments%20for%20purchases%20above%20%2435%20or%2C%20eventually%2C%20push%20the%20payment%20to%20a%20later%20date.%20In%20a%20press%20release%20announcing%20the%20agreement%2C%20company%20executives%20said%20it%20was%20intended%20to%20make%20%26quot%3Bconvenience%20even%20more%20accessible%26quot%3B%20for%20consumers%20and%20offer%20payment%20options%20that%20were%20%26quot%3Bessential%20to%20meeting%20our%20customers'%20needs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20announcement%2C%20um%2C%20raised%20some%20eyebrows.%20On%20the%20one%20hand%2C%20it's%20a%20free%20country%2C%20and%20anyone%20is%20welcome%20to%20pay%20for%20a%20burrito%20taxi%20in%20%2410%20installments%20over%20a%20month%20and%20a%20half.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20this%20scenario%20might%20involve%20more%20risk%20than%20reward%20for%20consumers%2C%20many%20of%20whom%20are%20already%20drowning%20in%20debt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20certainly%20doesn't%20seem%20like%20a%20positive%20development%20except%20for%20Klarna%20and%20maybe%20DoorDash%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Robert%20Lawless%2C%20a%20law%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Illinois%20who%20specializes%20in%20consumer%20finance.%20%26quot%3BI%20just%20don't%20think%20it's%20an%20advisable%20way%20to%20be%20paying%20for%20your%20DoorDash.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20BPNL%20industry%2C%20which%20includes%20companies%20such%20as%20Afterpay%2C%20Affirm%2C%20and%20Klarna%2C%20has%20taken%20off%20in%20recent%20years.%20The%20total%20value%20of%20loans%20originated%20by%20the%20industry%20jumped%20from%20%242%20billion%20in%202019%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.consumerfinance.gov%2Fabout-us%2Fnewsroom%2Fcfpb-study-details-the-rapid-growth-of-buy-now-pay-later-lending%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%2424%20billion%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202021%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffiles.consumerfinance.gov%2Ff%2Fdocuments%2Fcfpb_BNPL_Report_2025_01.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%2434%20billion%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202022%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Consumer%20Financial%20Protection%20Bureau.%20BNPL%20was%20initially%20seen%20mostly%20as%20an%20option%20for%20large-ish%20purchases%20%E2%80%94%20maybe%20a%20Peloton%20bike%2C%20if%20you're%20still%20into%20that%2C%20or%20a%20couch.%20The%20flexibility%20can%20be%20useful%2C%20by%20splitting%20payments%20into%20smaller%2C%20what%20might%20be%20more%20manageable%20amounts%2C%20and%20charging%20zero%20interest%20if%20payments%20are%20made%20on%20time.%20Buy%20now%2C%20pay%20later%20companies%20often%20do%20not%20do%20extensive%20credit%20checks%20as%20credit%20card%20companies%20do%2C%20meaning%20the%20option%20may%20be%20more%20accessible%20to%20some%20consumers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20optionality%20and%20ease%20of%20use%20helped%20BNPL%20boom%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20but%20in%20recent%20years%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.emarketer.com%2Fcontent%2Fus-bnpl-user-growth-continues-through-2028-slows%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egrowth%20has%20slowed%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20an%20effort%20to%20reignite%20expansion%2C%20companies%20have%20increasingly%20been%20allowing%20(and%20encouraging)%20consumers%20to%20use%20it%20on%20smaller-dollar%20and%20more%20trivial%20purchases%2C%20even%20groceries.%20In%20terms%20of%20consumer%20finance%2C%20it's%20a%20disturbing%20sign%20that%20some%20people%20might%20need%20to%20put%20essentials%20on%20payment%20plans.%20But%20businesses%20aren't%20just%20offering%20BNPL%20out%20of%20the%20kindness%20of%20their%20hearts%3B%20it's%20because%20they%20think%20they%20can%20make%20money%20off%20of%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20seeing%20it%20for%20smaller%20and%20smaller%20and%20smaller%20purchases%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Anastasiya%20Ghosh%2C%20a%20marketing%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Arizona.%20%26quot%3BPart%20of%20it%20is%20driven%20by%20these%20partnerships.%20So%20you%20see%20more%20and%20more%20merchants%20like%20DoorDash%20that%20are%20willing%20to%20participate%20and%20engage%2C%20which%20to%20me%20signals%20there%20is%20a%20revenue%20stream.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20the%20way%20BNPL%20companies%20make%20money%20is%20through%20merchant%20fees%2C%20where%20the%20platform%20that%20actually%20books%20the%20sale%20pays%20a%20fee%20to%20the%20payment%20partner%2C%20like%20Klarna%20or%20Affirm.%20This%20is%20similar%20to%20credit%20card%20swipe%20fees%2C%20but%20the%20payouts%20tend%20to%20be%20even%20higher.%20Businesses%20sign%20up%20for%20merchant%20fees%20because%20giving%20consumers%20expanded%20payment%20options%20like%20BNPL%20makes%20them%20likelier%20to%20buy%20and%20increases%20the%20size%20of%20their%20baskets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20works%20on%20our%20optimistic%20view%20of%20ourselves%20in%20the%20future.%20Obviously%2C%20in%20the%20future%2C%20maybe%20my%20income%20stream%20would%20improve%20or%20I%20would%20stick%20to%20my%20budget%20better%2C%26quot%3B%20Ghosh%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20%3Cem%3Ethat%20%3C%2Fem%3Edifferent%20from%20the%20psychology%20around%20credit%20cards%2C%20but%20we've%20also%20had%20years%20of%20consumer%20education%20around%20their%20risks.%20With%20BNPL%2C%20not%20so%20much.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBuy%20now%2C%20pay%20later%20users%20tend%20to%20be%20in%20more%20precarious%20spots%20than%20the%20average%20consumer.%20A%20June%202023%20survey%20by%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20New%20York%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flibertystreeteconomics.newyorkfed.org%2F2023%2F09%2Fwho-uses-buy-now-pay-later%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efound%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20women%2C%20renters%2C%20people%20without%20college%20degrees%2C%20low-income%20people%2C%20and%20those%20with%20lower%20credit%20scores%20were%20more%20likely%20to%20report%20having%20used%20BNPL%20in%20the%20previous%20year.%20BNPL%20may%20also%20make%20people's%20finances%20worse%3A%20Its%20users%20have%20been%20found%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpapers.ssrn.com%2Fsol3%2Fpapers.cfm%3Fabstract_id%3D4230633%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esee%20fast%20increases%20in%20bank%20overdraft%20charges%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20credit%20card%20interest%20and%20fees%20compared%20with%20consumers%20who%20don't%20use%20the%20option.%20The%20use%20of%20buy%20now%2C%20pay%20later%20has%20been%20linked%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdownload.ssrn.com%2F23%2F09%2F06%2Fssrn_id4564082_code5420949.pdf%3Fresponse-content-disposition%3Dinline%26X-Amz-Security-Token%3DIQoJb3JpZ2luX2VjEGoaCXVzLWVhc3QtMSJIMEYCIQDgo6lpv77K%252BzFYIqMIwetr%252BgQoOl4Zdz7S6m3HOFdwSgIhAI3yrf19DW4Bj2PvNOrk3NJn%252Fxr5R8NHTfEgXkukMb4MKscFCMP%252F%252F%252F%252F%252F%252F%252F%252F%252F%252FwEQBBoMMzA4NDc1MzAxMjU3IgyfXumtRsvJFHPXG1gqmwUQG%252FnBq%252FFxEWQjcaUbtiAFrIWHvoAZpGZcNndplO27Xfp1d4%252BxHYHR8gORRpf2HVy7P7UcUV4gYuqjj696BHrAjHMCeZLlPQc%252F5Hq596Ye4%252B7wejYalrZDJwH4jS8ZCVtmQ2PELt0HSqtEhuvBzKPgfjsXnckNum2masup129vB62G1h1doeCz6EYx1ykVcJ8RwVFxCou7gBazGgZJzZhYEQHpbFQ8mAW4vx9eh59zBjNecRMpVBNi5hjhsVT8B%252Fy9yuki6lkQERkyvE7%252BhtGrWUduhqHl5Y3MVUEZqcZmXZMuo5bKMF%252Fg6A2jTZgJjpiEuPsgeVim%252FasJTh8clGZXESzlm%252BblLadPRZhUkFRwgOcuY%252FQ8YUodEHnz8wphVYPA%252FKmyT8xNoJ%252F59Y7Q6EEB