%20their%20land%20to%20growing%20thirsty%20crops%2C%20including%20rice%2C%20wheat%2C%20and%20onion.%20These%20crops%20not%20only%20drink%20up%20more%20water%20but%20suck%20up%20even%20more%20nutrients.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20six-month%20investigation%20into%20understanding%20the%20impact%20of%20growing%20water-guzzling%20crops%20revealed%20that%20the%20top%20three%20states%20primarily%20growing%20water-intensive%20crops%20have%20depleted%20groundwater%20levels%20and%20soil%20nutrition%2C%20adding%20to%20the%20cost%20of%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESoil%20samples%20collected%20from%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20Gujarat%20and%20Rajasthan%20were%20found%20to%20be%20severely%20lacking%20both%20macro%20and%20micronutrients%2C%20especially%20nitrogen%2C%20potassium%2C%20iron%20and%20sulphur.%20One%20in%20five%20samples%20reported%20sulphur%20deficiency%20compared%20to%20one%20in%2010%20in%20states%20focusing%20on%20non-water-intensive%20crops.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENot%20just%20this%2C%20nearly%20nine%20in%2010%20soil%20samples%20in%20the%20top%20three%20states%20growing%20water-intensive%20staple%20food%20crops%20showed%20nitrogen%20deficiency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20absence%20of%20nutrients%20in%20the%20soil%20results%20in%20less%20nutritious%20food%20crops%20which%20in%20turn%20have%20a%20domino%20effect%20on%20your%20health.%20While%20you%20may%20eat%20vegetables%20and%20fruits%20thinking%20they%20are%20rich%20in%20essential%20proteins%2C%20vitamins%20and%20minerals%2C%20they%20might%20be%20lacking%20all%20or%20some%20of%20them%20because%20of%20the%20depleted%20soil.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20three-part%20series%2C%20we%20explore%20the%20impact%20of%20cultivating%20water-guzzling%20crops%20on%20groundwater%20use%2C%20soil%20health%2C%20and%20potentially%20human%20well-being.%20In%20the%20first%20part%20of%20the%20three-part%20series%2C%20we%20explored%20the%20impact%20on%20groundwater.%20It%20can%20be%20read%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsip-by-sip-water-guzzling-crops-drain-indias-groundwater-7997301%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20this%20second%20part%2C%20we%20look%20at%20the%20health%20of%20the%20soil%20and%20the%20food%20grown%20on%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStates%20dependent%20on%20water-intensive%20crops%20have%20poorer%20soil%20health%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20comparison%20of%20states%20growing%20water-intensive%20crops%20versus%20those%20growing%20non-water-intensive%20crops%20reveals%20a%20striking%20difference%20in%20soil%20health.%20The%20top%20three%20states%20-%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20Gujarat%20and%20Rajasthan%20-%20with%20the%20highest%20area%20share%20devoted%20to%20water-intensive%20crops%20have%20significantly%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.google.com%2Fspreadsheets%2Fd%2F1uX6ASO7YnwFU6bdD7x0FqIEvlDRdmhbHbkhQxsWDw6c%2Fedit%3Fgid%3D1029303647%23gid%3D1029303647%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elower%20levels%20of%20essential%20nutrients%20in%20soil%3C%2Fa%3E%20compared%20to%20those%20growing%20non-water-intensive%20crops%20-%20Jharkhand%2C%20Odisha%20and%20Tripura.%20Here%20are%20the%20key%20findings%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EOn%20average%2C%20nine%20in%2010%20soil%20samples%20in%20water-intensive%20crop-growing%20states%20were%20reported%20to%20have%20non-optimal%20nitrogen%2C%20a%20key%20nutrient%20for%20plants.%20Whereas%2C%20this%20figure%20was%20six%20in%2010%20in%20non-water-intensive%20crop-growing%20states.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ESimilar%20levels%20of%20phosphorus%20deficiency%20were%20reported%20in%20two%20groups%20of%20states%20-%2028.03%20per%20cent%20in%20water-intensive%20crop%20growing%20states%20compared%20to%2024.68%20per%20cent%20in%20non-water-intensive%20crop%20growing%20states.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EStates%20with%20a%20larger%20proportion%20of%20area%20under%20cultivation%20for%20water-intensive%20crops%20have%20twice%20the%20levels%20of%20potassium%20deficiency%20than%20states%20primarily%20growing%20non-water-intensive%20crops.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FYbUiF%2F9%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22The%20top%20three%20states%20%E2%80%93%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20Gujarat%20and%20Rajasthan%20%E2%80%93%20with%20the%20highest%20share%20of%20area%20devoted%20to%20water-intensive%20crops%20have%20significantly%20higher%20macronutrient%20deficiency%20in%20soil%20%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22597%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ESulphur%20deficiency%20was%20almost%20twice%20(20.60%20per%20cent)%20as%20prevalent%20in%20states%20growing%20water-intensive%20crops%20compared%20to%20those%20focusing%20on%20non-water-intensive%20crops%20(11.09%20per%20cent).%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIron%20deficiency%20was%20significantly%20higher%20in%20water-intensive%20crop%20states%2C%20with%20a%2036%20percentage%20point%20difference%20compared%20to%20non-water-intensive%20crop%20states%2C%20where%20iron%20deficiency%20levels%20were%20much%20lower.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FgajIo%2F10%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%221%20in%204%20soil%20samples%20in%20states%20primarily%20growing%20water-intensive%20crops%20is%20deficient%20in%20iron%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22436%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIntensive%20irrigation%20leads%20to%20soil%20salinisation%2C%20compaction%20and%20erosion%2C%20nutrient%20leaching%2C%20reduced%20microbial%20activity%20and%20waterlogging.%20Poor%20soil%20health%20leads%20to%20reduced%20crop%20yields%2C%20low-quality%20produce%2C%20and%20increased%20costs%20for%20farmers%20and%20low%20farm%20income%2C%26quot%3B%20explains%20Dr%20Ashok%20Kumar%2C%20an%20agronomist%2C%20at%20the%20FAO.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStaple%20or%20non-staple%2C%20water-guzzling%20crops%20leave%20soil%20undernourished%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGrowing%20staple%20foods%20that%20require%20a%20lot%20of%20water%20appears%20to%20be%20even%20worse%20for%20the%20soil%20than%20growing%20other%20types%20of%20water-intensive%20crops.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFarmers%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%20have%20devoted%20over%20half%20of%20their%20land%20under%20cultivation%20to%20water-intensive%20staple%20crops%20like%20rice%2C%20potatoes%20and%20millet.%20Farmers%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20and%20Punjab%20have%20dedicated%20nearly%20half%20of%20their%20land%20to%20other%20water-guzzling%20staples.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20Goa%20has%20the%20highest%20share%20of%20area%20under%20cultivation%20dedicated%20to%20water-intensive%20non-staple%20crops%2C%20using%20just%20over%20half%20of%20its%20agricultural%20land%20to%20grow%20crops%20like%20sweet%20potatoes%2C%20walnuts%2C%20nutmeg%20and%20oilseeds.%20Gujarat%20and%20Rajasthan%20follow%20with%20about%20a%20quarter%20of%20their%20land%20under%20cultivation%20for%20non-staple%20crops%20such%20as%20bananas%2C%20berries%2C%20nutmeg%2C%20and%20pepper.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20crop%20profile%20has%20a%20large%20influence%20on%20their%20current%20soil%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fflo.uri.sh%2Fvisualisation%2F21423933%2Fembed%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Interactive%20or%20visual%20content%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpublic.flourish.studio%2Fvisualisation%2F21423933%2F%3Futm_source%3Dembed%26utm_campaign%3Dvisualisation%2F21423933%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_top%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Made%20with%20Flourish%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpublic.flourish.studio%2Fresources%2Fmade_with_flourish.svg%5C%22%3E%20%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESoil%20in%20the%20top%20three%20states%20growing%20water-intensive%20staple%20food%20crops%20was%20found%20to%20be%20more%20deficient%20in%20nitrogen%20and%20sulphur%20than%20those%20growing%20water-intensive%20non-staple%20crops.%20Nearly%20nine%20out%20of%2010%20soil%20samples%20showed%20nitrogen%20deficiency.%20Whereas%2C%20about%20one%20in%20four%20samples%20showed%20sulphur%20deficiency%2C%20as%20per%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.google.com%2Fspreadsheets%2Fd%2F1uX6ASO7YnwFU6bdD7x0FqIEvlDRdmhbHbkhQxsWDw6c%2Fedit%3Fgid%3D240978204%23gid%3D240978204%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESoil%20Health%20Card%202023-24%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20we%20give%20excess%20water%20to%20the%20soil%2C%20there%20is%20a%20chance%20of%20nutrient%20leaching%20and%20loss%20of%20nutrients%2C%20particularly%20mobile%20nutrients%20like%20nitrogen%2C%26quot%3B%20explains%20Dr%20Ashok%20Kumar%20Patra%2C%20the%202022%20Glinka%20World%20Soil%20Prize%20Winner.%20%26quot%3BNitrogen%20is%20highly%20dynamic%20in%20the%20soil.%20Additionally%2C%20sandy%20soil%20has%20low%20nutrient%20retention%2C%26quot%3B%20adds%20Dr%20Patra%2C%20an%20Emeritus%20Scientist%20%26amp%3B%20Former%20Director%20of%20ICAR-Indian%20Institute%20of%20Soil%20Science%2C%20Bhopal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20these%20states%20fare%20slightly%20better%20on%20other%20key%20nutrients%20with%20a%20marginal%20difference%20in%20the%20proportion%20of%20soil%20samples%20reporting%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.google.com%2Fspreadsheets%2Fd%2F1uX6ASO7YnwFU6bdD7x0FqIEvlDRdmhbHbkhQxsWDw6c%2Fedit%3Fgid%3D240978204%23gid%3D240978204%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ephosphorus%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20potassium%20and%20zinc%20deficiency.%20For%20instance%2C%20three%20in%2010%20samples%20showed%20phosphorous%20deficiency%20as%20compared%20to%20four%20in%2010%20samples%20from%20non-staple%20food%20crop%20growing%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%2035%20per%20cent%20of%20soil%20samples%20in%20states%20growing%20water-intensive%20staple%20crops%20showed%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.google.com%2Fspreadsheets%2Fd%2F1uX6ASO7YnwFU6bdD7x0FqIEvlDRdmhbHbkhQxsWDw6c%2Fedit%3Fgid%3D38110413%23gid%3D38110413%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ezinc%3C%2Fa%3E%20deficiency%2C%20which%20is%20lower%20than%20the%2040%20per%20cent%20in%20states%20growing%20water-intensive%20non-staple%20crops.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FvxUR3%2F11%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Staple%20or%20non-staple%2C%20water-guzzling%20crops%20leave%20soil%20undernourished%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22527%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20chain%20reaction%20set%20off%20by%20water-intensive%20farming%20that%20leaches%20key%20nutrients%20from%20soil%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESoil%20health%20depends%20on%20its%20physical%2C%20biological%20and%20chemical%20properties.%20Nitrogen%2C%20an%20element%20often%20washed%20away%20in%20the%20irrigation%20of%20thirsty%20plants%2C%20is%20key%20for%20soil%20fertility.%20This%20also%20impacts%20other%20key%20elements%20critical%20to%20soil%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESoil%20in%20the%20top%20three%20states%20with%20the%20highest%20area%20under%20water-intensive%20crops%20was%20found%20to%20be%20extremely%20deficient%20in%20nitrogen%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.google.com%2Fspreadsheets%2Fd%2F1uX6ASO7YnwFU6bdD7x0FqIEvlDRdmhbHbkhQxsWDw6c%2Fedit%3Fgid%3D1798226351%23gid%3D1798226351%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESoil%20Health%20Card%202023-24%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E99%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20soil%20samples%20tested%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%20and%20Rajasthan%20were%20found%20to%20have%20either%20low%20or%20high%20nitrogen%20levels.%20In%20Gujarat%2C%20eight%20in%2010%20soil%20samples%20reported%20non-optimal%20nitrogen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNitrogen%20is%20present%20in%20both%20biological%20and%20mineral%20forms.%20At%20any%20time%2C%20if%20you%20have%20excess%20nitrogen%20somewhere%2C%20except%20biological%2C%20it%20escapes%20into%20the%20atmosphere%20as%20ammonia%20and%20gas%2C%26quot%3B%20explains%20Ajai%20Pachori%2C%20Joint%20Director%2C%20Agriculture%20(Chemistry)%2C%20Government%20of%20Rajasthan.%20He%20adds%2C%20%26quot%3BSecondly%2C%20mineral%20nitrogen%2C%20which%20we%20provide%20through%20fertilizer%2C%20can%20leach%20because%20of%20excessive%20water%20usage.%20It%20can%20leach%20beyond%20the%20roots%20and%20pollute%20water.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDenitrification%20is%20another%20process%20that%20causes%20nitrogen%20loss%20in%20waterlogged%20soil.%20%26quot%3BAs%20water%20moves%20downward%20through%20the%20soil%2C%20nitrate%20easily%20travels%20with%20it%2C%20often%20sinking%20below%20the%20plant%20root%20zone.%20While%20phosphorus%20doesn't%20leach%20as%20much%2C%20other%20nutrients%20like%20sulphur%2C%20calcium%2C%20and%20magnesium%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20move%20downward%20with%20the%20water.%20Excessive%20irrigation%20can%20carry%20dissolved%20metals%20deeper%20into%20the%20soil%20as%20well.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-03%2Fsgai3flo_farming-generic_625x300_25_March_25.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Pachori%20recommends%20that%20one-third%20of%20the%20nitrogen%20requirement%20should%20come%20from%20organic%20material%20in%20the%20form%20of%20farmyard%20manure%20and%20compost.%20Three-fourth%20of%20the%20nitrogen%20requirement%20should%20be%20met%20by%20fertilisers%20-%20either%20urea%20or%20ammonium%20sulphate%20or%20DAP%20(Diammonium%20Phosphate).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20as%20Dr%20Pachori%20said%2C%20farmers%20are%20using%20DAP%20more%20than%20required.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20average%2C%20eight%20in%2010%20samples%20in%20the%20three%20states%20had%20non-optimal%20potassium%20in%20the%20soil.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENearly%20one-third%20of%20the%20soil%20samples%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%20have%20non-optimal%20phosphorus.%20Four%20in%2010%20soil%20samples%20in%20Gujarat%20and%20one%20in%2010%20in%20Rajasthan%20had%20non-optimal%20phosphorus.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BStates%20using%20more%20water%20for%20irrigation%20give%20higher%20yields%20and%20take%20up%20more%20nutrients%20from%20the%20soil%2C%26quot%3B%20explains%20Dr%20Ashok%20Kumar%20Patra%2C%202022%20Glinka%20World%20Soil%20Prize%20winner.%20%26quot%3BBut%20if%20farmers%20don't%20add%20an%20equal%20amount%20of%20nutrients%20to%20the%20soil%2C%20there%20will%20be%20a%20nutrient%20deficiency%2C%26quot%3B%20adds%20Dr%20Patra%2C%20an%20Emeritus%20Scientist%20%26amp%3B%20Former%20Director%20of%20ICAR-Indian%20Institute%20of%20Soil%20Science%2C%20Bhopal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExcessive%20irrigation%20can%20lead%20to%20loss%20of%20nutrients%20from%20the%20soil%2C%20leaving%20it%20less%20fertile.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FFvEAO%2F5%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Soil%20samples%20in%20states%20primarily%20growing%20water-intensive%20crops%20reported%20higher%20nitrogen%20and%20potassium%20deficiency%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22274%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20soil%20in%20his%20field%20has%20a%20light%20texture%2C%20Kala%20Khan%2C%20a%20farmer%20residing%20in%20the%20Alwar%20district%20of%20Rajasthan%20has%20applied%20fertiliser%20like%20DAP%20and%20urea%20to%20fulfill%20the%20phosphorus%20and%20nitrogen%20requirements.%20Fellow%20farmer%20Bijendra%20Kumar%20often%20adds%20more%20urea%20to%20compensate%20for%20the%20water%20shortfall.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20rise%20in%20the%20quantity%20of%20phosphorous%20results%20in%20micronutrient%20(zinc%20and%20iron)%20deficiency%20in%20soil.%20Phosphorous%20and%20zinc%20and%20iron%20have%20an%20antagonistic%20effect%2C%26quot%3B%20Dr%20Pachori%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExcessive%20DAP%20dries%20up%20the%20soil%2C%20reduces%20water-holding%20capacity%2C%20makes%20soil%20alkaline%20and%20destroys%20micro-organisms%20and%20bacteria%20in%20the%20soil%2C%20added%20SP%20Yadav%2C%20Agriculture%20Research%20Officer%2C%20Soil%20Testing%20Laboratory%2C%20Alwar%2C%20Rajasthan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20three%20top%20water-intensive%20crop%20growing%20states%20have%20mixed%20results.%20In%20Rajasthan%2C%20over%20half%20of%20the%20soil%20samples%20showed%20deficiencies%20in%20both%20iron%20and%20zinc%2C%20while%208%20per%20cent%20also%20displayed%20a%20lack%20of%20sulphur.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20in%20Gujarat%2C%20one-fifth%20of%20the%20soil%20samples%20were%20found%20deficient%20in%20sulphur.%2029%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20soil%20samples%20had%20iron%20deficiency%20while%2037%20per%20cent%20had%20zinc%20deficiency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne-third%20of%20the%20soil%20samples%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%20reported%20sulphur%20deficiency.%2040-45%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20sample%20had%20iron%20and%20zinc%20deficiency%2C%20as%20per%20the%20Soil%20Health%20Card%202023-24.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F2gTl9%2F5%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Over%20half%20of%20the%20soil%20samples%20in%20Rajasthan%20showed%20deficiencies%20in%20both%20iron%20and%20zinc%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22274%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFive%20years%20ago%2C%20Rajasthan's%20soil%20was%20more%20deficient%20in%20zinc.%20Now%20it%20is%20iron%20deficient.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20because%20our%20department%20supplies%20zinc.%20Farmers%20too%20shell%20out%20some%20money%20and%20buy%20zinc%20supplements%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Mr%20Yadav.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20consequences%20of%20poor%20soil%20on%20plant%20health%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELack%20of%20soil%20nutrients%20directly%20impacts%20plant%20growth%20-%20both%20in%20terms%20of%20quality%20and%20quantity.%20Micronutrients%20iron%20and%20zinc%20act%20as%20catalysts%20and%20support%20various%20metabolic%20activities.%20%26quot%3BIron%20and%20zinc%20deficiency%20in%20soil%20can%20lead%20to%20retarded%20growth%2C%20less%20production%2C%20and%20low%20quality%20of%20produce%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Ajai%20Pachori%2C%20Joint%20Director%2C%20Agriculture%20(Chemistry)%2C%20Government%20of%20Rajasthan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EZinc%20also%20helps%20plants%20in%20an%20uptake%20of%20nutrients%20like%20calcium%20and%20chlorophyll%20formation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESulphur%2C%20another%20micronutrient%2C%20aids%20in%20the%20growth%20of%20oilseeds%20and%20pulses.%20Sulphur%20deficiency%20in%20the%20soil%20can%20lead%20to%20protein%20deficiency%20in%20pulses%2C%20said%20SP%20Yadav.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLet's%20say%20you%20grow%20pulses%20on%20soil%20lacking%20sulphur.%20The%20harvested%20crop%20will%20look%20like%20a%20regular%20pulse%3B%20when%20cooked%2C%20it%20will%20appear%20and%20taste%20like%20any%20other.%20However%2C%20it%20won't%20meet%20your%20protein%20needs%2C%20as%20the%20sulphur%20deficiency%20in%20the%20soil%20has%20caused%20it%20to%20lack%20essential%20protein%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENitrogen%2C%20a%20macronutrient%2C%20plays%20a%20key%20role%20in%20plant%20germination.%20%26quot%3BThe%20plant's%20body%2C%20which%20develops%20from%20the%20seed%2C%20is%20composed%20of%20nitrogen.%20The%20main%20role%20of%20nitrogen%20is%20to%20increase%20greenery%2C%20and%20plant%20growth%2C%26quot%3B%20adds%20Mr%20Yadav.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPhosphorus%2C%20a%20co-macronutrient%2C%20helps%20develop%20roots%20and%20grain%20formation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20job%20of%20potassium%20is%20to%20increase%20production%20quality%20and%20protect%20crops%20from%20diseases%20and%20pests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSoil%20health%20manifests%20directly%20with%20micronutrient%20deficiencies%20within%20the%20food%20items%2C%20which%20could%20be%20cereals%2C%20pulses%2C%20fruits%20and%20vegetables%2C%20etc%2C%26quot%3B%20explains%20Dr%20Rajiv%20Tandon%2C%20Consultant%20Paediatrician%20and%20Executive%20Director%2C%20The%20Health%20Continuum.%20He%20adds%2C%20%26quot%3BAnd%20that%20eventually%20leads%20to%20the%20same%20low%20levels%20of%20minerals%20and%20vitamins%20in%20the%20people%20who%20eat%20that%20particular%20food%20item.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERestoring%20soil%20health%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bottom%20line%20is%20that%20states%20growing%20water-intensive%20crops%20have%20bad%20soil%20health.%20Thirsty%20crops%20take%20up%20more%20nutrients%20than%20less%20thirsty%20crops%20and%20vice%20versa.%20Therefore%2C%20sustainable%20farming%20practices%20play%20a%20vital%20role%20in%20maintaining%20and%20improving%20soil%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFarmers%20are%20being%20taught%20to%20use%20fertilisers%20judiciously%20and%20apply%20farmyard%20manure%20to%20maintain%20soil%20health.%20Mr%20Yadav%20explained%2C%20%26quot%3BFarmers%20often%20have%20livestock%2C%20but%20don't%20utilize%20their%20manure%20effectively.%20Typically%2C%20it's%20spread%20on%20the%20soil%2C%20where%20it's%20exposed%20to%20pollution%20and%20extreme%20heat%2C%20causing%20it%20to%20dry%20out.%20When%20it%20rains%2C%20the%20nutrients%20are%20washed%20away%2C%20and%20the%20manure%20doesn't%20decompose%20properly%2C%20limiting%20its%20potential%20benefits.%20However%2C%20by%20digging%20a%20pit%20to%20store%20the%20manure%2C%20soil%20retains%20moisture%20throughout%20the%20year.%20Microorganisms%20can%20break%20it%20down%20more%20efficiently%2C%20transforming%20it%20into%20valuable%20vermicompost.%20This%20process%20enhances%20the%20soil's%20physical%2C%20chemical%2C%20and%20biological%20properties.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-03%2Fbrj8mfs_onion-crop_625x300_25_March_25.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20synergy%20between%20water%20and%20nutrients%2C%20opines%20Dr%20Ashok%20Kumar%20from%20FAO.%20%26quot%3BCrop%20rotation%2C%20such%20as%20alternating%20cereals%20with%20legumes%2C%20can%20enrich%20the%20soil%20with%20nitrogen%20for%20future%20crops.%20Similarly%2C%20rotating%20water-intensive%20crops%20with%20deep-rooted%20crops%20can%20help%20break%20compacted%20soil%20layers%20formed%20by%20the%20cultivation%20of%20water-intensive%20crops.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20shallow-rooted%20crops%20help%20prevent%20soil%20erosion.%20This%20will%20enhance%20soil%20structure%20and%20improve%20soil%20infiltration%20and%20retention%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20farmers%20dig%20deeper%20to%20irrigate%20their%20fields%2C%20they%20encounter%20saline%20water%20that%20isn't%20ideal%20for%20crops.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20saline%20water%20accumulates%20in%20the%20topsoil%2C%20it%20leads%20to%20soil%20salinity%2C%20which%20hampers%20germination.%20Let's%20say%20a%20seed%20germinates%20regardless%20of%20salinity%2C%20the%20plant's%20growth%20will%20be%20retarded.%20The%20roots%20won't%20develop%20properly%2C%20which%20affects%20the%20flowering%20and%20fruiting%20stages%2C%26quot%3B%20added%20Mr%20Yadav.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20restore%20soil%20health%2C%20Dr%20Ashok%20Kumar%20suggests%20adopting%20sustainable%20irrigation%20practices%20such%20as%20micro-irrigation%2C%20monitoring%20soil%20moisture%20levels%2C%20and%20implementing%20crop%20rotation%20and%20diversification%20to%20maintain%20soil%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20many%20ways%20to%20restore%20soil%20health%20in%20areas%20affected%20by%20intensive%20irrigation%20such%20as%20no-till%20farming%2C%20adding%20organic%20matter%2C%20planting%20cover%20crops%2C%20crop%20rotation%2C%20bioremediation%20and%20integrated%20nutrient%20management%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20article%20is%20part%20two%20of%20a%20three-part%20series%20on%20the%20impact%20of%20growing%20water-guzzling%20crops%20on%20groundwater%2C%20soil%20nutrition%20and%20health.%20In%20the%20first%20part%2C%20we%20looked%20at%20the%20depleting%20groundwater.%20It%20can%20be%20read%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20third%20part%2C%20we%20explore%20the%20link%20between%20soil%20nutrition%20and%20human%20health.%20Read%20the%20part%20three%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMethodology%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20data%20story%20looks%20at%20the%20impact%20of%20growing%20water-intensive%20crops%20on%20groundwater%2C%20soil%20health%20and%20human%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20begin%20with%2C%20the%20author%20looked%20at%20the%20%26quot%3BMekonnen%2C%20M.M.%20and%20Hoekstra%2C%20A.Y.%20(2010)%20The%20green%2C%20blue%20and%20grey%20water%20footprint%20of%20crops%20and%20derived%20crop%20products%26quot%3B%20report%20to%20identify%20water-intensive%20crops%20in%20states%20across%20India.%20The%20author%20considered%20only%20blue%20water%20footprint%20data%20to%20know%20how%20much%20groundwater%20is%20being%20used%20to%20irrigate%20a%20crop%2C%20in%20a%20state.%20If%20a%20state%20uses%20more%20blue%20water%20than%20the%20national%20average%20to%20grow%20a%20certain%20crop%2C%20then%20the%20author%20considered%20the%20crop%20%26quot%3Bwater-intensive%26quot%3B%20in%20that%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20author%20also%20looked%20at%20the%20%26quot%3BArea%2C%20Production%20%26amp%3B%20Yield%20-%20Reports%26quot%3B%20from%202013-2023%20to%20calculate%20the%20proportion%20of%20area%20under%20cultivation%20of%20water-intensive%20or%20non-water-intensive%20crops%20in%20each%20state.%20The%20area%2C%20production%20and%20yield%20reports%20were%20taken%20from%20the%20official%20website%20of%20the%20Directorate%20of%20Economics%20and%20Statistics%2C%20Department%20of%20Agriculture%20and%20Farmers%20Welfare%2C%20Ministry%20of%20Agriculture%20%26amp%3B%20Farmers%20Welfare.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20this%20methodology%2C%20the%20author%20identified%20three%20states%20with%20the%20highest%20proportion%20of%20area%20under%20cultivation%20for%20water-intensive%20crops%20and%20three%20states%20with%20the%20highest%20proportion%20of%20area%20under%20cultivation%20for%20non-water-intensive%20crops.%20They%20then%20looked%20at%20Soil%20Health%20Card%20data%20(2023-24)%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Agriculture%20and%20Farmers%20Welfare.%20They%20focused%20on%20the%20status%20of%20macronutrients%20(N%2C%20P%2C%20K)%20and%20micronutrients%20(S%2C%20Fe%2C%20Zn)%20in%20the%20soil%20to%20see%20if%20the%20soil%20in%20states%20growing%20water-intensive%20crops%20is%20more%20deficient%20in%20essential%20nutrients.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20author%20also%20looked%20at%20the%20National%20Family%20Health%20Survey%20(NFHS-5)%20data%20specifically%20for%20the%20six%20states%20and%20analysed%20data%20for%20key%20health%20indicators%20-%20malnutrition%20and%20anaemia%20among%20children%20under%20five%20and%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20supporting%20data%20and%20analysis%20can%20be%20accessed%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.google.com%2Fspreadsheets%2Fd%2F1Fl5uKcofimHXMaNVLzXYDjf0JJrwV5vkkA6uFz0lTKA%2Fedit%3Fgid%3D0%23gid%3D0%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20author%20travelled%20to%20Alwar%20district%20in%20Rajasthan%20and%20met%20farmers%20in%20different%20villages%20to%20understand%20their%20challenges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Reporting%20for%20this%20story%20was%20supported%20by%20the%20Environmental%20Data%20Journalism%20Academy-%20a%20program%20of%20Internews'%20Earth%20Journalism%20Network%20and%20Thibi.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742880600000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-03%2F9c1js9c_raj